            {# How to use #}
            <article class="card p-2">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h2>üß© How to use</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p class="p-1">
                        Add <code class="text-bold text-primary">data-js="collapse"</code> to the button and set
                        <code class="text-bold text-primary">data-target</code> to the ID of the matching
                        <code class="text-bold text-primary">.accordion-body</code>. The script toggles the panel and updates
                        <code class="text-bold text-primary">aria-expanded</code> automatically.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </article>

            {# How it works #}
            <article class="card p-2">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h2>üß© How it works</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p class="p-1">
                        The script listens to clicks on elements with <code class="text-bold text-primary">data-js="collapse"</code>.
                        It reads <code class="text-bold text-primary">data-target</code>, finds the matching <code
                            class="text-bold text-primary">.accordion-body</code>,
                        and adds or removes <code class="text-bold text-primary">.show</code>. The open/close animation
                        is 300ms.
                        Extra clicks are ignored during the animation.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </article>

            {# Note about colors #}
            <article class="card p-2">
